        skos:altLabel "FRR"@en,
        skos:definition "False referral rate measures the proportion of patients without the disease who are incorrectly flagged for further confirmatory evaluation by the test. It is computed as the number of false positive results divided by the total number of individuals examined. This metric complements diagnostic yield by indicating the potential burden of unnecessary follow-up procedures and associated harms."@en,
