    Annotations: 
        rdfs:comment "(1) Describes whether the data cover a complete population or sample. If a sample, describes the set from which the data were drawn.
(2) Describes if the data are representative of the larger set (e.g., geographic coverage), and how representativeness was verified; if not representative, describes why not.
(3) Describes any subpopulations (by age, sex, diagnosis), how they are identified, and their distributions within the dataset."@en,
        rdfs:label "muestreo"@es,
        rdfs:label "sampling"@en,
        rdfs:label "抽样"@zh,
        skos:altLabel "representativeness"@en,
        skos:altLabel "sample population"@en,
        skos:definition "Describes how the data that form the dataset were selected."@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        roadmap:ROADMAP_03381
    
    
Class: roadmap:ROADMAP_03397

