    Annotations: 
        rdfs:comment "For example, if a Partition has 500 male patients and 600 female patients, one could list two Subsets to indicate those two groups.  One also could indicate a Subset of 1100 patients to cover the entire Partition.

A Subset has one of more Count values (e.g., number of patients, number of images) and one or more Patient descriptors (age, sex, etc.)"@en,
        rdfs:label "subconjunto"@es,
        rdfs:label "subset"@en,
        rdfs:label "子集"@zh,
        skos:definition "A subset is all or part of a dataset or partition: it is used to describe the demographics of the entity of which it's a part."@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        roadmap:ROADMAP_00001,
        roadmap:ROADMAP_00130 some roadmap:ROADMAP_00055
    
    
Class: roadmap:ROADMAP_03477

